replies.body:
Hello, 

I had this problem recently and i tried to investigate. Look at the first line of your logs :

> Riot::RADS::Common::ZLibHelper::DecompressFile: C:/jenkins/workspace/rads-code-win-release/code/Solutions/RiotRADS/Source/RADS/Common/ZLibHelper.cpp(230): Failed to do inflate operation with return value **-1**

This is a message from the un-zip system from the LOL patcher. The patcher in fact download files that are zipped, and unzip then before process them.

According to [ZLib documentation](https://github.com/if1live/haruna/blob/master/sora/io/zip_helper.cpp#L135-L140) : 
- Value -1 mean "Error while opening the zipfile for reading, or error while writing uncompressed file". This mean that you may have no space left on your hard drive for instance.
- Value -3 mean "The file i am trying to un-zip is corrupted", which mean they was a network error during dowload of the patch.
- Value -4 mean "Not enought RAM avaliable for un-zip operation", which mean your computer is garbage

*Unspecified Error* usually happens during the *patching* process and is influenced by an *unstable connection* to the patching servers themselves. I'd recommend working through our [**connection guide**](https://support.riotgames.com/hc/en-us/articles/201752664-Troubleshooting-Connection-Issues), as it covers common network misconfigurations that can cause this issue to occur.

Let me know if those steps helped.
